S6 SCENARIO
You are integrating a Hugging Face transformer pipeline into your food delivery app to
automatically generate polite responses to customer reviews in real time, at a rate of
several hundred requests per minute.
Question: Explain what the attention mechanism in transformers enables that traditional
RNN-based models could not do effectively with long text sequences. Describe one practical
challenge of running a transformer model in a high-traffic production environment and one
common way to mitigate it.

(Answer)
The attention mechanism is a key feature of transformer models that allows the model to focus on the most relevant words in a sentence while processing the entire text at the same time. Unlike traditional RNN-based models, which process words sequentially and often struggle to retain information from long text sequences, transformers can capture relationships between words that are far apart. This enables them to better understand context and generate more accurate and meaningful responses.

A practical challenge of deploying a transformer model in a high-traffic production environment is its high computational cost. Processing several hundred requests per minute requires significant CPU or GPU resources, which can increase response time and operational costs.

One common way to mitigate this challenge is model optimization, such as using a smaller transformer model or applying model quantization. These techniques reduce the model's size and computation requirements while maintaining good performance, allowing the application to handle more requests with lower latency and improved scalability.